1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )
2
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:45,280
{\an8}- God is the Greatest.
- God is the Greatest.

3
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:21,400
{\an8}If Farez had been with us,

4
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,800
{\an8}together with Holy Dragon,

5
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:27,480
{\an8}we would've been much more unstoppable.

6
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,600
He was a good man.

7
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:35,040
He only made one mistake.

8
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:38,600
Falling in love with Radwa.

9
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,560
But if it weren't for Radwa,

10
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:45,880
he would've died long ago.

11
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,760
Falling in love isn't wrong.

12
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:51,560
Being obsessed with something
that was not his

13
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:53,720
was his mistake.

14
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:56,160
The fate of our lives

15
00:01:58,520 --> 00:02:00,200
comes with a choice.

16
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,680
Come to terms with it.

17
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,960
Let Radwa be happy with Ridz.

18
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:11,039
Farez had that choice.

19
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:31,120
I'm sorry, Farez.

20
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,680
Goodbye, friend.

21
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:49,839
DEBT 100K

22
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:52,520
Husziya Raudhah Binti Husaini!

23
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:55,439
You've had your fun with that RM100,000!

24
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:57,320
And you want to escape?

25
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,680
Mom.

26
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:06,760
Open this door now before I break it down!

27
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,519
Woman!

28
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:12,120
Can't you hear me?

29
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:14,640
Open this door now!

30
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:20,039
Mom.

31
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:23,319
I'm giving you two days.

32
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:25,320
If you don't settle this debt,

33
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,400
you'll die.

34
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:29,520
Arif!

35
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:35,040
WHERE'S OUR 100K
PAY IT BACK IF YOU WANT TO LIVE

36
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,720
All this is your fault, Mom!

37
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,319
You treated Radwa like an animal!

38
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:44,320
He's not even leaving us a cent!

39
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:48,839
You won't even let Dad contact Radwa!

40
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:51,560
You didn't let him do that
until he left us!

41
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,239
Radwa will laugh seeing us like this!

42
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,600
This is your fault!

43
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,880
You don't care about Radwa!

44
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:03,159
Shut up!

45
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:04,720
Insolent!

46
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,880
Is Thariq Ridzuwan really my husband?

47
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,320
The doctor said you can be discharged.

48
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,840
We'll go home to our house, okay?

49
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:50,719
Never mind, we'll go to
Mom's house if you're not ready.

50
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:53,280
- All right?
- Can I ask you something?

51
00:04:57,160 --> 00:05:01,240
Will you be mad if I still don't believe
you're my husband?

52
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,400
No.

53
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,360
Why would I be mad?

54
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,079
Why aren't you mad?

55
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,360
Aren't you upset?

56
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:12,160
No.

57
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,360
Because the Radwa I know is intelligent.

58
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:19,160
She's not easily influenced by others.

59
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,960
All right, get some rest.

60
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,200
Let me do the work.

61
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,520
What work?

62
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:38,000
To continue the love story of my treasure.

63
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:45,279
If you want to trust me,

64
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,920
don't use this.

65
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:49,520
But use this.

66
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,600
How?

67
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,839
Sweetie, I'm here.

68
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:59,240
Go to your mom.

69
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,440
Sorry, sweetie.

70
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:12,360
Sorry for scaring you that night.

71
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,760
I'm so sorry.

72
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:40,400
Peace be upon you.

73
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,520
Darling, come in.

74
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,000
Welcome home.

75
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,480
Darling.

76
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:05,080
Every atom in me misses you
so much, my treasure.

77
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:10,960
Do you know

78
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:15,079
I did not change a single piece
of furniture in this house?

79
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:16,680
Especially this one.

80
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,800
Your favorite spot.

81
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,040
Why?

82
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:29,440
Because I don't want to lose
a single memory of us in this house.

83
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,440
Where's my room?

84
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,200
Your room is upstairs.

85
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,919
Yes, love.

86
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,679
I promise

87
00:07:56,680 --> 00:08:00,040
she will become our Husniya Radwa again.

88
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:04,240
I promise.

89
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,000
Thariq?

90
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,680
Thariq?

91
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:19,960
Thariq?

92
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:26,080
"Radwa, please wear this outfit. Please!"

93
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,360
Thariq?

94
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,520
Peace be upon you.

95
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,720
Did anyone order a ride?

96
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:50,160
And peace be upon you.

97
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:52,959
What are you doing?

98
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:55,039
I've come to save you.

99
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,759
Save me from what?

100
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:59,280
To save you
from being forced to marry Adib.

101
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,199
- Who is Adib?
- It doesn't matter.

102
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:04,079
Okay, let's go.

103
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:07,559
- Come on.
- Where are we going?

104
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,039
Running away.

105
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,880
Running away?

106
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:13,920
What are you doing?

107
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:17,159
Do you remember that
you were once a runaway bride?

108
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:18,639
Remember?

109
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,399
No, I don't remember.

110
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:23,279
I don't need to wear this outfit
if you're trying to make me remember.

111
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:25,160
It's hot, you know!

112
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:28,600
Why are you wearing a uniform?
What's up with you?

113
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,399
Do you know what? Come on!

114
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:35,159
- Come... Slow down!
- Come.

115
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,680
What if I fall?

116
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:39,280
Are you afraid of falling?

117
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,960
I'm afraid of falling.

118
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:45,639
Then I'll catch you.

119
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,120
You have my word.

120
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:52,560
Your anger made me forget
how much I missed you.

121
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,320
Do I always get mad?

122
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:02,879
No, you get mad for a reason.

123
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,280
Just like now.

124
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:07,959
Why am I mad now?

125
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:10,520
Why are you mad now? Because of this.

126
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,319
This.

127
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,920
You're hungry, right?

128
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,959
How do you know?

129
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,120
I...

130
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:21,840
know you very well.

131
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:24,560
Every moment of the day.

132
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:28,840
Shall we eat?

133
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,640
Do you want to eat chicken?

134
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,720
Come on. I think we have to catch one.

135
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,560
Fried chicken.

136
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,679
Why is there so much?

137
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,159
What?

138
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:48,359
The chicken? These?

139
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,440
This is too much for you?

140
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,639
This isn't much for you. Do you know why?

141
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:55,000
Because there's a ghost behind you.

142
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,719
- Just kidding.
- Is there?

143
00:10:58,720 --> 00:10:59,800
I'm just kidding.

144
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,200
Not funny? It was a little funny.

145
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,719
Darling.

146
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,920
Okay.

147
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,159
I have something serious to tell you.

148
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:12,600
You have to promise me
that you'll be open to it.

149
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,360
- Okay?
- Okay.

150
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,560
<i>If your house is on fire</i>

151
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,200
<i>Call the fire brigade</i>

152
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:25,400
Your angry heart is like
the fire burning the house.

153
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:30,199
The fire brigade will pour water
on the burning house.

154
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,920
<i>For an angry heart</i>

155
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,400
<i>One fried chicken, please</i>

156
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,399
What?

157
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,319
What did you just say?

158
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,839
Just now?

159
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:46,440
That's the most
legendary poem in Malaysia.

160
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:50,639
Your poem is so stupid.

161
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:51,600
Stupid?

162
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:55,920
But never mind, I like that.

163
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:59,240
Can I go to the toilet?

164
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,800
Go on.

165
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:05,040
Just a second.

166
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:12,240
This chicken is quite delicious.

167
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:26,680
Hi, Husniya Radwa. How are you?

168
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:31,000
She's drenched.

169
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:35,040
Poor thing, she's soaked.

170
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:40,120
Why did you pour water on me?

171
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,560
Are you a cleaner?

172
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,960
But you can't be cleaners,
your clothes are too nice.

173
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:50,560
What now?

174
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:55,479
- Hurry.
- Why are you panicking now?

175
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,960
I'm okay.

176
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,680
But I don't understand
why you poured water.

177
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,999
Darling!

178
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,920
Are you okay? Okay, breathe.

179
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:14,240
Follow me. T-H-A-R-I-Q.

180
00:13:15,560 --> 00:13:17,000
Why must I spell your name?

181
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:24,320
Because...

182
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,879
Darling.

183
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:28,839
I don't want you to have
a panic attack, okay?

184
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:31,640
Breathe. Please, breathe.

185
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:33,720
Am I having a panic attack?

186
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:37,640
Do you have asthma?
Because you seem to be having one now.

187
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:41,039
Asthma?

188
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:44,600
I don't have asthma,
but I do have scoliosis.

189
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:48,280
Did you tell Ginger One and Ginger Two
to pour water on me?

190
00:13:49,560 --> 00:13:51,600
Ginger One? Ginger...

191
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,800
Did you do all this to trigger my memory?

192
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,439
Right?

193
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:05,600
It wasn't me.

194
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,399
Haider! All this is Haider's plan!

195
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:13,679
His plan was stupid, right? You're soaked.

196
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:15,280
Here.

197
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:20,440
Whoever listened to him
is an even bigger idiot.

198
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:26,120
Where did you find those extras?

199
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:31,320
They're not extras.
They're my friends while I was studying.

200
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:35,400
You used to hate both of them back then.

201
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,359
I hired them to come here.

202
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:41,600
Maybe the people you hate
could've triggered your memory.

203
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,440
That's why I did this.

204
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:49,240
Luckily, they ran out of ice.

205
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:52,680
I told them to use iced water initially.

206
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,960
I wouldn't be able to handle it
with the air conditioner and all.

207
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,600
I'm sorry.

208
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,599
You're lucky you're good-looking.

209
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,520
But you're an idiot.

210
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,600
I'm good?

211
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:14,440
So...

212
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:17,720
this is where I proposed to you.

213
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,520
By the lake?

214
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:24,000
That's pretty cringe.

215
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,840
Cringe. That's why you rejected me.

216
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,000
Why?

217
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:31,680
Who's Rangga?

218
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:35,800
I'm Thariq Ridzuwan.

219
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,879
I don't know.

220
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:40,920
But the important thing is,
I didn't give up.

221
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:44,520
I ended up becoming
Husniya Radwa's husband.

222
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:57,960
Thariq, can you look at me?

223
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:00,240
Yes. Why?

224
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:05,360
I truly appreciate your effort
to trigger my memory.

225
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:08,760
Although it was idiotic
to pour water and all that.

226
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:11,840
But what if I really cannot remember?

227
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,920
We'll start over.

228
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:18,800
I'll win you back again.

229
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:22,120
For how long?

230
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,800
Forever.

231
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:28,520
I know that feeling will return.

232
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:31,560
If it doesn't?

233
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,560
Sorry.

234
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:47,839
I didn't mean to upset you by saying that.

235
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:51,239
But I'm just confused now.

236
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,360
I feel lost.

237
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:00,080
Darling.

238
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,840
I...

239
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:06,800
will love you forever.

240
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:11,280
Even if you don't love me anymore,

241
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,800
and even if we're not together anymore,

242
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,520
I'll accept it.

243
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:24,000
I understand you need time.

244
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:29,480
As long as you're happy and are okay,

245
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,000
it's fine.

246
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:36,560
Back then,

247
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,240
you told me

248
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:45,240
I'm the greatest blessing
God has given you.

249
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:48,600
That you love me so much.

250
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:51,920
Very much.

251
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,680
More than you love yourself.

252
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:03,920
And I know you're honest.

253
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:09,320
Because you've never lied about feelings.

254
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:15,720
And what you've felt before is in here.

255
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:21,720
And I give you my word.

256
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:25,280
That feeling will return.

257
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,520
I will never

258
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:33,880
give up on you.

259
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:39,240
I will never give up on us.

260
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:41,920
I promise.

261
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:49,839
I may not be able to remember you yet.

262
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:51,240
Yes.

263
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:54,600
But when I look at you,

264
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,680
listen to you speak,

265
00:18:59,080 --> 00:19:00,840
and hear these words,

266
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:04,639
it would not be hard

267
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:08,520
for someone to fall in love
with Thariq Ridzuwan, right?

268
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:19,680
The other day, I...

269
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:26,720
Go upstairs first.

270
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:30,719
- Separate rooms, right?
- Separate rooms.

271
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:32,360
Go and rest, okay?

272
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:44,119
Okay, boys.

273
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:48,200
How are we going
to restore Radwa's memory?

274
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:50,560
I've got an idea.

275
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:54,040
It's a little rough, but it might help.

276
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:56,800
- What do we need to do?
- Not us.

277
00:19:58,040 --> 00:19:59,640
Kevin.

278
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:02,799
Hold on. I was just about to drink.

279
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,160
Kevin?

280
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:06,600
