00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:01,360
But I'm still your daughter.

558
00:40:03,080 --> 00:40:04,880
A child should forgive her mother.

559
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:08,440
Not the other way around, right?

560
00:40:15,360 --> 00:40:17,120
I mean it, Mom.

561
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:22,080
I forgive you.

562
00:40:26,040 --> 00:40:27,720
Dear.

563
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:32,360
In all your life as a mother,

564
00:40:34,840 --> 00:40:38,400
you've never done anything good
for our children.

565
00:40:39,160 --> 00:40:41,440
Ridha ran away.

566
00:40:42,720 --> 00:40:44,800
Raudhah is dead.

567
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,960
And our son

568
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:50,960
was kidnapped.

569
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:53,799
And to this day,

570
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:58,360
we still don't know
whether he's alive or dead.

571
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:02,880
The only one who is left

572
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,440
is Radwa.

573
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:08,480
Radwa is right here.

574
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:11,800
Please.

575
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:16,360
Please do good for our daughter

576
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:19,040
for the last time.

577
00:41:20,160 --> 00:41:24,000
To avoid becoming a failure as a mother.

578
00:41:38,640 --> 00:41:40,640
I...

579
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:44,280
won't allow

580
00:41:45,040 --> 00:41:46,560
you

581
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:49,560
to forgive me.

582
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:53,639
Mom?

583
00:41:53,640 --> 00:41:55,480
But...

584
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:58,880
But...

585
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:03,400
I...

586
00:42:05,840 --> 00:42:06,960
forgive...

587
00:42:10,760 --> 00:42:12,120
Mom?

588
00:42:14,560 --> 00:42:15,840
Mom.

589
00:42:16,520 --> 00:42:17,759
Mom.

590
00:42:17,760 --> 00:42:21,400
Mom!

591
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:23,560
Mom...

592
00:42:25,560 --> 00:42:27,320
All my life,

593
00:42:28,560 --> 00:42:30,800
I've wanted only one thing.

594
00:42:33,880 --> 00:42:36,800
I wanted you to forgive me.

595
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,000
That's all.

596
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:51,120
Uncle, we'll take our leave now.

597
00:42:52,160 --> 00:42:53,399
Peace be upon you.

598
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:54,760
And peace be upon you.

599
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:01,440
Come on.

600
00:43:07,600 --> 00:43:09,040
I'm going to the car.

601
00:43:09,760 --> 00:43:11,120
I'll wait for you there.

602
00:43:12,560 --> 00:43:13,920
Dad.

603
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:29,720
Radwa.

604
00:43:32,760 --> 00:43:35,080
You're still my daughter, right?

605
00:43:36,640 --> 00:43:39,720
I'll love you for eternity.

606
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:43,880
Dad.

607
00:43:44,800 --> 00:43:47,120
Let me take care of you.

608
00:43:52,280 --> 00:43:54,759
{\an8}- This is delicious.
- All of this

609
00:43:54,760 --> 00:43:56,679
{\an8}was cooked by me.

610
00:43:56,680 --> 00:44:00,199
Megat, do you believe
Ridz cooked these dishes?

611
00:44:00,200 --> 00:44:01,839
No, I think the baby cooked.

612
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:03,959
- What do you mean?
- What?

613
00:44:03,960 --> 00:44:07,279
- What do you mean by that?
- Fried chicken...

614
00:44:07,280 --> 00:44:08,600
Guys!

615
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:13,919
I've got a very big announcement
to make today.

616
00:44:13,920 --> 00:44:15,760
Why? Are you getting married?

617
00:44:18,360 --> 00:44:22,599
I know that as a Malaysian,
I should know how to speak Malay.

618
00:44:22,600 --> 00:44:23,999
Yes, correct.

619
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:25,959
It is our national language.

620
00:44:25,960 --> 00:44:27,639
- Right?
- Yes.

621
00:44:27,640 --> 00:44:28,999
Thalia.

622
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:30,759
My apologies for saying this.

623
00:44:30,760 --> 00:44:32,599
Haider.

624
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:37,640
He used your toothbrush
to scrub the toilet clean.

625
00:44:38,560 --> 00:44:39,440
That's not all.

626
00:44:40,120 --> 00:44:43,000
He placed the toothbrush back
for you to brush your teeth.

627
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:44,960
Seriously?

628
00:44:48,480 --> 00:44:50,720
Boss, your little brother here.

629
00:44:52,360 --> 00:44:53,800
You hung out at the mamak that day, right?

630
00:44:54,680 --> 00:44:57,999
He had just eaten
five soft-boiled eggs, boss!

631
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:00,039
And ate stink beans too.

632
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:03,719
Then he farted on your cheese naan, boss!

633
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:05,560
And you ate it!

634
00:45:06,360 --> 00:45:08,960
You farted on my cheese naan.

635
00:45:09,560 --> 00:45:10,679
You, Megat!

636
00:45:10,680 --> 00:45:12,759
You keep laughing.

637
00:45:12,760 --> 00:45:14,120
You're crazy about divorced women.

638
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:17,280
- And rejected by them too!
- True.

639
00:45:21,480 --> 00:45:22,520
He likes divorced women.

640
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:25,560
I know all of you

641
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:30,679
thought this whole time
that I've been quiet and clueless.

642
00:45:30,680 --> 00:45:32,600
I don't know how to speak Malay.

643
00:45:33,200 --> 00:45:34,680
Because I want to tell all of you

644
00:45:36,080 --> 00:45:37,160
that you're idiots.

645
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:39,560
Idiots!

646
00:45:44,600 --> 00:45:46,759
Enough. Megat!

647
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:48,600
Ridz, that's enough.

648
00:45:50,680 --> 00:45:52,879
- Take that.
- You deceived us.

649
00:45:52,880 --> 00:45:55,040
Sorry, guys!

650
00:45:55,760 --> 00:45:57,120
Okay, guys.

651
00:45:58,200 --> 00:46:00,960
Remember, we're the Holy Dragon.

652
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:03,080
We're all brothers.

653
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:06,000
Promise me

654
00:46:06,600 --> 00:46:08,520
we'll remain like this forever.

655
00:46:09,800 --> 00:46:11,559
Promise me, boys.

656
00:46:11,560 --> 00:46:13,999
- Promise me.
- Yes, promise.

657
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:15,680
Come on.

658
00:46:19,760 --> 00:46:22,640
- Until death.
- Until death.

659
00:46:28,920 --> 00:46:30,360
Thank you

660
00:46:31,520 --> 00:46:33,120
for being my hero.

661
00:46:34,120 --> 00:46:36,000
For always protecting me.

662
00:46:37,200 --> 00:46:38,680
Protecting us.

663
00:46:40,880 --> 00:46:42,400
Darling.

664
00:46:43,040 --> 00:46:44,800
I want you to know

665
00:46:45,760 --> 00:46:48,400
that you will always be my treasure.

666
00:46:54,480 --> 00:46:56,799
We know you're in the special forces.
Can you help?

667
00:46:56,800 --> 00:46:58,720
What's wrong? Help with what?

668
00:46:59,320 --> 00:47:01,039
I was just having a moment with my wife.

669
00:47:01,040 --> 00:47:03,960
Help us, please!
A child fell into the lake.

670
00:47:04,720 --> 00:47:06,279
- Oh my God!
- Why aren't you helping?

671
00:47:06,280 --> 00:47:09,200
Because there's a crocodile!

672
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:11,279
I'll go now, okay?

673
00:47:11,280 --> 00:47:12,680
Hurry!

674
00:47:16,280 --> 00:47:18,000
Take the baby and go home.

675
00:47:19,680 --> 00:47:21,359
- Go home, okay?
- Okay.

676
00:47:21,360 --> 00:47:22,840
Dear.

677
00:47:24,680 --> 00:47:26,000
I...

678
00:47:26,840 --> 00:47:28,120
I believe

679
00:47:28,760 --> 00:47:31,959
there's nothing you can't conquer.

680
00:47:31,960 --> 00:47:33,320
Even if it's a crocodile.

681
00:47:38,440 --> 00:47:40,359
Come back safe, Thariq Ridzuwan.

682
00:47:40,360 --> 00:47:41,679
I will.

683
00:47:41,680 --> 00:47:43,599
My hero.

684
00:47:43,600 --> 00:47:44,880
My love.

685
00:47:52,920 --> 00:47:54,439
{\an8}Crocodile.

686
00:47:54,440 --> 00:47:55,719
{\an8}THE END

687
00:47:55,720 --> 00:47:57,480
{\an8}I'm coming for you.

